headline: TXN's Analog Revenue Growth Picks Up: A Sign of More Upside?
summary: Texas Instruments' analog unit, driving 77.6% of revenues with 17.9% growth in Q2 2025, is gaining from 5G and broad industrial demand.

headline: Wolfspeed Is Walking The Tightrope: Turnaround And Liquidity In Question
summary: Wolfspeed, Inc. faces restructuring to cut debt by 70%, amid market headwinds and rising risks. Click for my updated look at WOLF stock post fiscal Q4 earnings.
